registered above ground,

01:43:06.750 --> 01:43:09.110
in funky bars rather

01:43:09.110 --> 01:43:13.890
than in exclusive unmarked
clubs visible only by the lines

01:43:13.890 --> 01:43:16.960
of people cued outside
in front of them.

01:43:16.960 --> 01:43:21.530
Indeed, the bar where these
reverberations were perhaps most

01:43:21.530 --> 01:43:25.390
keenly felt was a sleazy
Mafia-run dive

01:43:25.390 --> 01:43:29.040
in New York City called
the Stonewall Inn,

01:43:29.040 --> 01:43:35.110 position:56%
the site of the famous Stonewall
rebellion of June 1969 which is said

01:43:35.110 --> 01:43:39.910
by many and its many, many
historians would agree

01:43:39.910 --> 01:43:44.370
that it get started the gay
liberation movement in America.

01:43:44.370 --> 01:43:50.430
Now, scholars have puzzled
over the Stonewall uprising.

01:43:50.430 --> 01:43:53.850
That it happened when it
did, and that it seemed

01:43:53.850 --> 01:43:57.120
to trigger this big movement.

01:43:57.120 --> 01:44:01.680
Some historians have argued that
by the time of the rebellion,

01:44:01.680 --> 01:44:05.940
there was already what was
called the Homophile Movement

01:44:05.940 --> 01:44:11.140
that had been active for almost
two decades with Frank Kameny

01:44:11.140 --> 01:44:15.680
who was a DC activist being
a leading figure in it.

01:44:15.680 --> 01:44:20.240
And research has shown that
indeed sexual minorities had taken

01:44:20.240 --> 01:44:24.900
to the streets before
Stonewall in one case in LA

01:44:24.900 --> 01:44:28.030
at a bar not far from where I live.

01:44:28.030 --> 01:44:31.040
Others have argued that if
gays and lesbians were open

01:44:31.040 --> 01:44:35.630
to movement making in '69, it was
because of their participation

01:44:35.630 --> 01:44:39.170
in bar culture which
had for decades put them

01:44:39.170 --> 01:44:42.080
on the front lines of
everyday resistance.

01:44:42.080 --> 01:44:45.720
Now, I want to make a different
but related argument and it's

01:44:45.720 --> 01:44:49.470
that what went on outside the
Stonewall and on those June nights,

01:44:49.470 --> 01:44:55.600
some 48 years ago, built on change
is already underway inside the

01:44:55.600 --> 01:44:57.680
Stonewall Inn.

01:44:57.680 --> 01:45:04.010
Now, the Stonewall was a gay
dancing bar which as late as 1969,

01:45:04.010 --> 01:45:08.520
that is at the height of the
'60s, was unusual in New York.

01:45:08.520 --> 01:45:12.840
Most of the city's gay male bars
did not permit dancing while the

01:45:12.840 --> 01:45:15.880
Stonewall actually
had two dance floors.

01:45:15.880 --> 01:45:21.670 position:56%
