suggest that the bar's dance floors,

01:45:21.670 --> 01:45:24.630
particularly the room in the
back which was frequented

01:45:24.630 --> 01:45:28.590
by African American and
Puerto Ricans street kids,

01:45:28.590 --> 01:45:32.870
undermined the sexual
indirection and repression

01:45:32.870 --> 01:45:38.490 position:56%
that characterized most other-- that
characterized most other gay bars.

01:45:38.490 --> 01:45:43.490
In that room, in that back room,
Judy Garland, was all ready passe,

01:45:43.490 --> 01:45:47.350
she was already a thing of
the past, as soul music blared

01:45:47.350 --> 01:45:52.080
on their jukebox and the
dancing there was not today.

01:45:52.080 --> 01:45:55.620
One of the many young street queens
who frequented the Stonewall argued

01:45:55.620 --> 01:45:57.420
that the culture that existed

01:45:57.420 --> 01:46:02.940
in the back room fostered the
articulation of gay desire.

01:46:02.940 --> 01:46:06.820 position:56%
He said at other gay bars, you know,
you could look across the room,

01:46:06.820 --> 01:46:09.260
you could see a sexy
guy, you could fantasize

01:46:09.260 --> 01:46:12.750
about getting involved but,
you know, you couldn't go

01:46:12.750 --> 01:46:15.480
over and ask him to dance.

01:46:15.480 --> 01:46:18.370
Another regular at the
bar credits the Stonewall

01:46:18.370 --> 01:46:21.520
with making him confront
his own sexual uptightness

01:46:21.520 --> 01:46:23.560
and internalize homophobia.

01:46:23.560 --> 01:46:28.200
So the Stonewall was itself
a site of transformation,

01:46:28.200 --> 01:46:30.500
one that was forging
a stronger connection

01:46:30.500 --> 01:46:34.520
between going out and coming out.

01:46:34.520 --> 01:46:38.900
It was also forging a relationship
between commercialized leisure

01:46:38.900 --> 01:46:42.700
and gay, what would become
gay liberation, an association

01:46:42.700 --> 01:46:45.490
that disco would build upon.

01:46:46.560 --> 01:46:50.620
Now, by the time music
writer, Vince Aletti,

01:46:50.620 --> 01:46:54.250
wrote about what he
called party music.

01:46:54.250 --> 01:46:58.330
Party music and discotheque
rock in the fall of '73

01:46:58.330 --> 01:47:01.190
in Rolling Stone magazine,
gay men had been dancing

01:47:01.190 --> 01:47:03.310
in discos for three years.

01:47:03.310 --> 01:47:05.730
It would take another year before

01:47:05.730 --> 01:47:10.520
