keeping track of hot dance clubs

01:47:10.520 --> 01:47:13.040
as it called, cuts
as they called it.

01:47:13.040 --> 01:47:17.950
And two more before the majors
began to take the music seriously.

01:47:17.950 --> 01:47:22.690
When one considers the context
in which gay disco took shape,

01:47:22.690 --> 01:47:25.920
one in which dancing had been
restricted, had been surveilled,

01:47:25.920 --> 01:47:29.630
had really been illicit, you
now it's nearly impossible

01:47:29.630 --> 01:47:33.450
to disaggregate dancing
from politics.

01:47:33.450 --> 01:47:35.620
Even if there had been no instances

01:47:35.620 --> 01:47:39.020
of DJ's leading dancers off the
dance floor and into the streets

01:47:39.020 --> 01:47:42.110
to protest, and this by
the way actually happened

01:47:42.110 --> 01:47:45.240
in 1971 in New York City.

01:47:45.240 --> 01:47:50.360
Dancing still constituted an act of
defiance for gay men and lesbians.

01:47:51.460 --> 01:47:56.000
Now, gay disco amplify the
shift towards greater sexual

01:47:56.000 --> 01:48:00.200
straightforwardness which
intend to-- with gay liberation,

01:48:00.200 --> 01:48:03.300
would change bar culture radically.

01:48:03.300 --> 01:48:08.350 position:56%
It would also change gay sociability
and gay male subjectivity.

01:48:08.350 --> 01:48:11.440
How they understood
themselves as they shift away

01:48:11.440 --> 01:48:15.910
from effeminacy to
macho accelerated.

01:48:15.910 --> 01:48:19.200
How did disco participate
in the shift?

01:48:19.200 --> 01:48:22.070
